                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111M72/7</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJE1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-31T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>376. Department’s 349, March 24, 6 p.m. Department has received further
                    information in regard to prisoners taken to Germany by auxiliary cruiser <hi
                        rend="italic">Moewe</hi> to the effect that at least 50 American citizens
                    are now held there. Urge the Foreign Office to obtain full report from Spanish
                    Ambassador, Berlin, as to their number, condition, and place of imprisonment,
                    and to instruct him to make every effort to secure their prompt release and
                    departure from Germany.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
